covered: Valid requests: Multiple success scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC19, TC20, TC21) validate default behavior, explicit offset/limit, and audit levels.
Empty responses: TC06 and TC07 verify behavior when no bundles exist or offset is beyond total (empty JSON array + 200).

Pagination basics and limits: TC01, TC02, TC05 validate default limit (up to 100), explicit offset/limit, returned counts and starting positions; TC07 covers offset beyond total; TC16/TC11 cover integer boundary and excessive limit cases.
Query parameter validation: Negative values (TC08, TC09), invalid audit (TC10), unexpected extra params (TC15), SQL-injection attempt (TC14), and integer-boundary checks (TC16) are exercised.

Authorization and error handling: TC12 covers missing/invalid token (401); TC13 and TC22 cover dependency failure/timeout (503/504); several TC’s assert proper 4xx handling for invalid parameters (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11).

Performance & Security: TC17 and TC18 address response-time expectations under load; TC14 addresses injection attack resilience; regression tests TC19/TC20 check previously fixed behaviors/backwards compatibility.
gaps: Caching behavior: No tests assert Content-Type, Cache-Control, ETag, or conditional GET behavior (If-None-Match -> 304).
Rate limiting / throttling: No tests for 429 responses or handling of client rate limits (burst requests, Retry-After header).
Schema validation: No tests validate that each returned object strictly conforms to the #/definitions/Bundle schema (required fields, types, nested objects).

Parameter type and edge-case validation: Missing tests for non-integer/ malformed types (e.g., offset=abc, limit=1.1), limit=0 (minimum allowed), and offset equal exactly to total count (boundary vs beyond).
Permission/authorization granularity: No tests for 403 Forbidden (valid token but insufficient permissions/roles) or separate handling of expired vs malformed tokens.
Pagination ordering/continuity: No tests ensuring deterministic ordering across pages (no duplicates/missing items when iterating pages) and consistency when concurrent writes occur.
Content negotiation: No tests for Accept header behavior or responses when non-JSON Accept headers are requested.
recommendations: Add tests asserting response headers: Content-Type: application/json, Cache-Control, ETag and a conditional GET test (If-None-Match -> expect 304 when unchanged).
Add rate-limiting tests: send burst requests to confirm 429 behavior and presence/semantics of Retry-After header (or documented alternative).
Introduce strict JSON schema checks against #/definitions/Bundle for multiple scenarios (single item, many items, nulls/optional fields) to ensure structural compliance.
Add parameter-type validation tests: offset=abc, limit=abc, offset=1.1, limit=0 and verify clear 4xx responses with explanatory error messages.
Add permission variation tests: 403 Forbidden for valid credentials lacking privileges, and distinguish expired vs malformed tokens (401 vs 403 as applicable).

Add pagination continuity tests: create a known ordered dataset and iterate pages verifying deterministic ordering, no overlap, and no missing items across adjacent pages; include a test where offset == total to assert empty array behavior.
Clarify and test audit parameter semantics (case-sensitivity and permitted values) and include a test for audit=NONE explicit vs omitted param equivalence.
Define and assert a server-side maximum limit (documented max page size) and add focused tests for values around that maximum (e.g., max, max+1) with explicit expected error and message.
